---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import InfoBox from '../components/InfoBox.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About The Breed | Elite BoerBoel"
  description="Learn about the BoerBoel breed - history, characteristics, and what makes them special."
  keywords="boerboel, boerboel, mini boerboel, boerboel breed, boerboel facts"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="About The Breed"
    subtitle="Discover what makes BoerBoels such beloved companions"
  />

  <section class="info-content">
    <div class="content-container">
      <h2>The BoerBoel: A Beloved Family Companion</h2>
      <p>BoerBoels — affectionate hybrid breeds blending the Poodle with Golden Retrievers, Old English Sheepdogs, and other gentle parent breeds — are among the most loving and family-friendly companions in the world. Their teddy-bear coats, intelligent minds, and warm-hearted nature make them an extraordinary fit for almost any home.</p>

      <h3>The BoerBoel Family</h3>
      <p>At Elite BoerBoel, we raise three closely related types:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>BoerBoels:</strong> Golden Retriever crossed with Poodle — friendly, affectionate, and easy to train.</li>
        <li><strong>BoerBoels:</strong> Old English Sheepdog crossed with Poodle — gentle, calm, and beautifully soft.</li>
        <li><strong>BoerBoels:</strong> A smaller, apartment-friendly version of the BoerBoel with the same loving temperament.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Physical Characteristics</h3>
      <p>BoerBoels vary in size depending on the parent breeds, but all share a soft, low-shedding, allergy-friendly coat.</p>

      <InfoBox type="info" title="Size">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mini BoerBoels:</strong> 12–35 lbs, 12–17 inches tall</li>
          <li><strong>Standard BoerBoels:</strong> 35–60 lbs, 17–22 inches tall</li>
          <li><strong>Standard BoerBoels:</strong> 55–70 lbs, 18–24 inches tall</li>
        </ul>
      </InfoBox>

      <InfoBox type="info" title="Coat">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Type:</strong> Wavy or curly, soft and plush</li>
          <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Regular brushing 2–3x per week, professional grooming every 6–8 weeks</li>
          <li><strong>Shedding:</strong> Low-shedding and considered allergy-friendly</li>
        </ul>
      </InfoBox>

      <h3>Colors and Patterns</h3>
      <p>Our boerboels come in a beautiful range of colors:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>BoerBoels:</strong> Cream, apricot, golden, red — solid or with light markings</li>
        <li><strong>BoerBoels:</strong> Classic black &amp; white, often with eye-catching parti patterns</li>
        <li><strong>BoerBoels:</strong> Black &amp; white with playful, photogenic markings</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Temperament</h3>
      <p>BoerBoels are known for their:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Affection:</strong> Wonderfully cuddly and people-focused</li>
        <li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> Quick learners thanks to the Poodle side</li>
        <li><strong>Family-friendliness:</strong> Gentle and patient with children of all ages</li>
        <li><strong>Sociability:</strong> Get along well with other dogs and pets</li>
        <li><strong>Adaptability:</strong> Thrive in apartments, homes, and active outdoor lifestyles alike</li>
        <li><strong>Sensitivity:</strong> Tune into their humans' moods — wonderful emotional companions</li>
      </ul>

      <InfoBox type="paw" title="Did You Know?">
        <p>BoerBoels are often chosen as therapy and emotional-support dogs because of their warm, intuitive nature and low-shedding coats — making them welcome in places where other breeds might not be.</p>
      </InfoBox>

      <h3>Life Expectancy</h3>
      <p>With proper care, boerboels typically live 12–15 years, making them a wonderful long-term companion for your family.</p>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Ready to Welcome a BoerBoel?</h3>
        <p>Browse our available puppies and find your perfect match.</p>
        <a href="/available-puppies" class="btn">View Available Puppies</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .info-content {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .content-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2B2018;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #5a5a5a;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    color: #5a5a5a;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary), var(--color-primary));
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    color: white;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .info-content {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
